      This is the third time I have stayed at Garden Place Hotel and once again I was not disappointed. Despite increasing competition in the town this remains my all-round favourite for location, facilities and value for...I’ve done it again! Stayed at Garden Place. It is as good as ever, clean and comfortable and with excellent food, cooked by Chef Theo and his team.Our thanks to Emmanuel for his welcome and to all the staff for...
      -The gardens are kept beautifully and are great and a safe place for children to explore -Breakfast is included and is plenty to set you up for the day -Free laundry after trekking is a nice touch, especially clea...We stayed with Alberto, Micheline and the Kevins for 2 nights. La Locanda is a very cozy place to stay. Alberto has several rooms, all uniquely decorated and with own veranda. The rooms are spatious and clean...
      A small but lovely swimming pool, a large open air lounge and dining area, spacious rooms with free wifi and TV are the typical amenities you would expect in a high end hotel, and they have them.The staff were fantastic. On the day I trekked to see Dian Fossey’s grave I didn’t get back to the hotel until 8 pm. I was exhausted after a really long day and the staff took such good care of me. After each trek...
      Breakfast was included and every morning there was fresh fruit, coffee, tea (the African tea was my favourite), bread, and a freshly cooked omelette.We spent five nights on this lovely campsite. The people were very welcoming and we mase new friends. The food was delicious and always custom made, the banana beer gave us the effects we wished for and the place...

      Relaxing in nature and comfort
      Our family loves Classic Lodge for its large property (can walk in and explore), for its landscaping which uses lots of natural-looking plants, flowers, and local stone, it’s helpful staff (we have gotten upgraded rooms a few times!). We love it’s pool which is usually uncrowded and very clean. Food is good. Hot showers are nice with lots of pressure. Downsides-bed began feeling too soft the second night.

      Brydenls wrote a review Jul 2019
      1 contribution
      A wonderful lodge with tons of potential
      I went to the volcano mountains for a day trip with my girlfriend and two other friends. On our way back we decided to stop at this wonderful lodge. The staff was remarkably welcoming, in particular their manager Paul, who took time out of his day to show us around the compound. He showed us multiple local fruits, plants used for herbal medicine, beekeeping, banana beer production, and we got our own sugar cane to eat. Admittedly, when we visited the resort, it was quiet, but as it is a new establishment this is to be expected. We stayed for food and drinks which were absolutely delicious and we cannot thank Paul enough for the time he spent showing us around this wonderful resort. Highly recommend to all travellers looking for a place to stay near the volcano mountains.…

      Not quite Classic Lodge
      I didn't stay at this hotel but visited the site to use the sauna and massage services. The property is quite large and has very good landscaping with modern facilities. There is a nice pool on site with a small gym and sauna room. The massage was not great. The locker room can use some expansion as there are only 2 shower stalls and 1 toilet (there are 2 urinals outside) which seem to be inadequate when I visited with the number of guests. It is a beautiful place located in a scenic area near Musanze. Staff can use more training as they don't seem to care or know what they are doing. Perhaps the hotel is quite new and hopefully will improve with time. It does have potential.…

      Best lodge in Rwanda
      Came with the family for one week vacation. The place is so relaxant, staff is welcoming and friendly, guest exclusivity, and professional service is utmost. I loved the Olympic size pool, played foot ball and basket ball. The most of all, had to visit the ecotourism products: beekeeping, banana beer production, horticulture, traditional healing, local food preparation, basket weaving and more.
